setwd("~/Desktop/Lab/Working_Projects/trapseq_2023")
suppressPackageStartupMessages(library("org.At.tair.db"))
suppressPackageStartupMessages(library(DESeq2))
library(clusterProfiler) #A universal enrichment tool for interpreting omics data #prettydoc?
library(readr)
library(tidyverse) #to use distinct 
library(pathview)
library(enrichplot)
library(dplyr)
library(tibble)
library(magrittr)
library(WGCNA)
library(ggrepel)
color_gene<- read_csv("turqgene_modules.csv") 
Rows: 849 Columns: 2 Column specification 
Delimiter: ","
chr (2): gene_id, colors
 Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
 Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
color_tb <- data.frame(color_gene, row.names = color_gene$gene_id ) 
keyid<-color_tb$gene_id

###add information to table
color_tb$symbol = mapIds(org.At.tair.db, 
                    keys=keyid, 
                    keytype= "TAIR" , 
                    column= "SYMBOL", 
                    multiVals= "first")
'select()' returned 1:many mapping between keys and columns
color_tb$entrez = mapIds(org.At.tair.db, 
                    keys=keyid, 
                    keytype="TAIR", 
                    column="ENTREZID", 
                    multiVals="first")
'select()' returned 1:1 mapping between keys and columns
colortb_genes<- color_tb$entrez
#GO enrichment refers specifically to gene ontology. GO provides the framework and set of concepts for describing the functions of gene products from all organisms.
eGO1 <- enrichGO(gene         = colortb_genes,
                OrgDb         = org.At.tair.db,
                keyType       = 'ENTREZID',
                ont           = "BP",
                pAdjustMethod = "BH",
                qvalueCutoff  = 0.01)
#eGO1
#The dotplot shows the number of genes associated with the first 50 terms (size) and the p-adjusted values for these terms (color). This plot displays the top 50 genes by gene ratio (# genes related to GO term / total number of sig genes), not p-adjusted value.
dotplot(eGO1, 
        x = "GeneRatio", 
        showCategory = 10,
        label_format = 30 , 
        color = "p.adjust") + 
  ggtitle("Dotplot for eGO")


goplot(eGO1 , 
       color = "p.adjust",
       showCategory = 3,
       geom = "text", 
       force = TRUE,
       repel = TRUE)


heatplot(eGO1, 
         showCategory = 30, 
         symbol = "rect",
         foldChange = NULL,
         pvalue = NULL,
         label_format = 30)


upsetplot(eGO1, 8)

###Reduce redundancy: Bc the nature of GO parent terms can show enrichment due to over rep child terms: to fix use simplify() function 
s_eGO1<-clusterProfiler::simplify(eGO1)

barplot(s_eGO1, color = "p.adjust") +
  ggtitle("s_GO Enrichment of Color Module genes") 


dotplot(s_eGO1, x = "GeneRatio", showCategory = 20,label_format = 70 , color = "p.adjust")+ ggtitle("s_GO Enrichment Dotplot for Color Module genes")


goplot(s_eGO1,
       showCategory = 3,
       color = "p.adjust",
       geom = "text", 
       force = TRUE,
       repel = TRUE)

#(count of core enrichment genes) / (count of pathway genes)

heatplot(s_eGO1, 
         showCategory = 30, 
         symbol = "rect",
         foldChange = NULL,
         pvalue = NULL,
         label_format = 30)


upsetplot(s_eGO1, 8)


gGO1 <- groupGO(gene= colortb_genes,
               OrgDb= 'org.At.tair.db',
               ont= "BP",
               level = 3,
               keyType = "ENTREZID",
               readable= TRUE)
head(gGO1)
cnetplot(gGO1, 
         showCategory=8,
         layout = "kk",
         circular = FALSE,
         node_label = "all",
         categorySize="p.adjust",
         order=TRUE,
         shadowtext = "all",)
